1. Open NetBeans → Create a new Java project
File → New Project
Choose: Java with Ant → Java Application
Name it: SeleniumTest

2. Add Selenium JARs
You must download Selenium:
✔ Download Selenium latest from here:
https://www.selenium.dev/downloads/
You will get a ZIP → extract it.
Inside, you will find a folder:
selenium-java-<version>/
   ├── selenium-java.jar
   ├── selenium-api.jar
   ├── ... (many JARs)
   └── libs/  (has more JARs)
Add all JARs:
NetBeans → Right-click your project → Properties
→ Libraries → Add JAR/Folder
→ Select:
everything inside the main folder
everything inside libs folder

3. Add ChromeDriver
Download ChromeDriver matching your Chrome version:
https://googlechromelabs.github.io/chrome-for-testing/
Put it inside your project folder:
SeleniumTest/
   ├── chromedriver.exe
   ├── src/
   └── nbproject/

4. Paste this code in NetBeans
 import org.openqa.selenium.WebDriver;
import org.openqa.selenium.edge.EdgeDriver;

public class FirstSeleniumPro {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        // Optionally set system property if needed:
        WebDriver driver = new EdgeDriver();
        try {
            driver.get("https://www.google.com");
            System.out.println("Title: " + driver.getTitle());
            Thread.sleep(10000); 
            driver.get("https://mgit.ac.in/");
// wait so you can see the browser
        } catch (Exception e) {
            System.out.println("Error: " + e.getMessage());
        } finally {
            driver.quit();
        }
    }
}


5. Click Run → It works
NetBeans handles everything for you.
